ian Literature in English''], p. 261, Columbia University Press, 2003, {{ISBN|0-231-12810-X}}, retrieved July 18, 2010</ref>\n* [[Adil Jussawalla]], ''Missing Person'',<ref>[http://india.poetryinternationalweb.org/piw_cms/cms/cms_module/index.php?obj_id=2714 \"Adil Jussawalla\"], Poetry International website, retrieved July 10, 2010</ref>\n* [[Jayanta Mahapatra]]:\n** ''A Father's Hours'', [[Calcutta]]: United Writers<ref name=iepcppm>Purnima Mehta, [https://books.google.com/books?id=7fsLY0b5aJAC&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false \"16. Jayanta Mahapatra: A Silence-bound Pilgrim\"], pp. 184-85, in Jaydipsinh Dodiya (ed.), ''Indian English Poetry: Critical Perspectives'', 2000, Delhi: Prabhat Kumar Sharma for Sarup & Sons, {{ISBN|81-7625-111-9}}; retrieved July 17, 2010</ref>\n** ''A Rain of Rites'', [[Athens, Georgia|Athens]], Georgia: University of Georgia Press<ref name=iepcppm/>\n* [[Arvind Krishna Mehrotra]], ''Nine Enclosures'',<ref>Mehrotra, Arvind Krishna (ed.), [https://books.google.com/books?id=OFvyBHXH-ssC&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false ''A History of Indian Literature in English'', p. 259], Columbia University Press, 2003, {{ISBN|0-231-12810-X}}, retrieved July 18, 2010</ref>\n* [[Meena Alexander]], ''The Bird's Bright Ring'', [[Calcutta]]: [[Writers Workshop]], [[India]].<ref name=mnkpipe>Naik, M. K., [https://books.google.com/books?id=FcH2MUnlQjQC&printsec=frontcover#PRA1-PA230,M1 ''Perspectives on Indian Poetry in English''], p. 230 (Abhinav Publications, 1984, {{ISBN|0-391-03286-0}}, {{ISBN|978-0-391-03286-6}}), retrieved June 12, 2009</ref>\n* [[Arundhathi Subramaniam]], ''Nine Enclosures'' (poetry in [[English language|English]]), [[Mumbai]]: Clearing House<ref>[http://india.poetryinternationalweb.org/piw_cms/cms/cms_module/index.php?obj_id=15316 \"Arundhathi Subramaniam\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721052941/http://india.poetryinternationalweb.org/piw_