joitusta''\n* [[Hannu M\u00e4kel\u00e4 (writer)|Hannu M\u00e4kel\u00e4]], ''Synkkyys pohjaton, ninn my\u00f6s iloni, onneni''\n* [[Jarkko Laine]], ''Viidenpennin Hamlet''\n* [[Matti Rossi]], ''Laulu tummana tulevi''\n* [[Matti Kuusi]], ''Kansanruno Kalevala'', a reconstruction of the folk poems that formed the basis of the Finnish national epic, ''Kaalevala'', compiled in [[1849 in poetry|1849]] by [[Elias L\u00f6nnrot]].\n\n===French language===\n\n====[[French poetry|France]]====\n* [[Anne-Marie Albiach]], ''Objet''<ref name=pa20cfv/>\n* [[Roland Bacri]], ''Roland Bacri'' (the name of the author and book are the same)\n* [[Herv\u00e9 Bazin]], ''Traits''\n* [[Jean Berthet]], ''L'\u00e9ternel instant''\n* [[Philippe Chabaneix]], ''Dix nouvelles romances''\n* [[Ren\u00e9 Char]], ''Aromates chasseurs'' (\"Hunter's Aromatic Herbs\")<ref>Denis Hollier (ed.), ''A New History of French Literature'', p. 1024, Cambridge, Massachusetts: Harvard University Press, 1989. {{ISBN|0-674-61565-4}}</ref>\n* [[Jean Daive]], ''Le jeu des s\u00e9ries sc\u00e9niques''<ref name=pa20cfv/>\n* [[Christian Dedeyan]], ''Chant du Houlme''\n* [[Roger Giroux]], ''Th\u00e9atre'', published posthumously (died [[1973 in poetry|1973]])<ref name=pa20cfv/>\n* [[Robert Houdelot]], ''Les Treize''\n* [[Edmond Jab\u00e8s]], Le Livre des Ressemblances''<ref name=pa20cfv/>\n* [[Jacques Marlet]], ''Toi qui p\u00e2lis au nom de Vancouver''\n* [[Robert Marteau]], ''Atlante''<ref name=pa20cfv/>\n* [[Jacques Pr\u00e9vert]], ''Grand Bal du printemps''\n* [[Raymond Queneau]], ''Morale \u00e9l\u00e9mentaire''\n* [[J. P. Seguin]], ''LAnn\u00e9e po\u00e9tique 1975''\n\n=====Criticism, scholarship and biography=====\n* [[John Edwin Jackson]], a study of [[Yves Bonnefoy]]\n\n====[[Canadian poetry|Canada]]====\n* [[Georges Cartier]], ''Chanteaux''\n* [[Paul Chanel Malenfant]], ''Po\u00e8mes de la m\u00e8res pays''\n* [[Marie Uguay]], ''Signe et rumeur''\n* A Quebec collective of women, ''La Nef des sorci\u00e8res''\n\n=