ub.htm Joe Rosenblatt: Publications],\" Canadian Poetry Online.</ref>\n* [[Charles Sangster]], ''Norland echoes and other strains and lyrics,'' ed. Frank M. Tierney (Tecumseh)<ref name=dcbo>Frank M. Tierney, \"[http://www.biographi.ca/009004-119.01-e.php?&id_nbr=6418 Sangster, Charles],\" Dictionary of Canadian Biography Online. Web., Oct. 15 2010.</ref>\n* [[Raymond Souster]], '' To Hell with Poetry''. Burton, Ohio.<ref name=rpo>\"[http://rpo.library.utoronto.ca/poet/513.html Notes on Life and Works] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110817195614/http://rpo.library.utoronto.ca/poet/513.html |date=2011-08-17 }},\" Selected Poetry of Raymond Souster, Representative Poetry Online, UToronto.ca, Web, May 7, 2011.</ref>\n;Anthologies\n* ''[[New Provinces (poetry anthology)|New Provinces]]'' reprinted\u2014first anthology of modernist poetry in Canada (originally published [[1936 in poetry|1936]]), including work by [[F. R. Scott]], [[E. J. Pratt]], [[Robert Finch (poet)|Robert Finch]], [[A. J. M. Smith]], [[Leo Kennedy]], [[A. M. Klein]].\n\n===[[Indian poetry|India]] in [[Indian poetry in English|English]]===\n* [[Arun Kolatkar]], ''Jejuri'', [[Bombay]]: Clearing House, [[India]].<ref name=\"books.google.com\"/>\n* [[Nissim Ezekiel]]:\n** ''Hymns in Darkness'', [[Delhi]], Oxford University Press<ref name=\"books.google.com\">Niranjan Mohanty, [https://books.google.com/books?id=7fsLY0b5aJAC&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false \"Trends in Indian Poetry in English\"], p. 18 (\"Works Cited\"), Footnote 7, in Jaydipsinh Dodiya (ed.), ''Indian English Poetry: Critical Perspectives'', 2000, Delhi: Prabhat Kumar Sharma for Sarup & Sons, {{ISBN|81-7625-111-9}}, retrieved July 17, 2010</ref>\n** ''Poster Prayers'',<ref>Anup C. Nair and Rajesh I. Patel, [https://books.google.com/books?id=7fsLY0b5aJAC&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false \"22. Nissim Ezekiel the Poet: A Bird's Eyeview\"], pp. 248, 257-5